Using Pycharm with Powershell


1. Launching Pycharm from Powershell
    .if on path, launch it with 
            pycharm .
    .if not, use full path 
        & "C:\Program Files\JetBrains\PyCharm 2025.3.1.1\bin\pycharm64.exe"
      or to a specific project 
        & "C:\Program Files\JetBrains\PyCharm 2025.3.1.1\bin\pycharm64.exe" "C:Users\edgar\python\powershell"   



2. Using Powershell inside Pycharm (recommended)
.python has a built-in terminal and I can switch it to Powershell
    .open Pycharm
    .go to file > settings > tools > terminal 
    .set shell path to:
        C:\Windows\System32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0\powershell.exe
    .click OK 
    .press alt + f12 to open the terminal - not its Powershell 

> it matters because I can run Python scripts with: 
    python script.py 

> I can install packages with:
    python -m pip install <package> 
>> I stay inside the IDE while using my preferred shell 



3. allowing Powershell to run python scripts 
.if Powershell blocks scripts inside pycharm, fix the execution policy:
    run Powershell as admin and execute:
        Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned
            press A to accept 

    .this allows:
        .python virtual environments to activate 
        .pycharm's terminal to run scripts normally 



4. running python scripts from powershell 
.if I want to run my pycharm project scripts directly from powershell:
        cd C:\path\to\project
        python main.py

.if using a virtual environment:
        .\venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
        python main.py
